OriginalText.Phrase: Laudamus te benedicimus te adoramus te

Note.EditorialCommentary: Passage cancelled in sources; alternative ending added later

OriginalText.Phrase: Gratias agimus tibit propter magnam gloriam

Note.EditorialCommentary: Cancelled text begins here: "domine deus agnus"

OriginalText.Phrase: Quoniam tu solus sanctus Tu solus dominus

Note.EditorialCommentary: This passage is apparently erroneous in all surviving sources, producing a chain of parallel fifths with the Bassus. It must remain open to question, however, whether this is a copying error, as suggested in this edition (stemming from a common ancestor of the extant witnesses), or a compositional error arising from an attempt to produce octave imitation between Bassus (m. 100) and Altus (m. 101) - a part-writing fault which, although particularly exposed here, is only one of many passages with parallel perfect consonances in this mass.
